  <entry>
    <title type="html"><![CDATA[Fire.app 1.0 is released]]></title>
    <link href="http://handlino.herokuapp.com/blog/2012/04/07/20594243839/"/>
    <updated>2012-04-07T00:00:00+08:00</updated>
    <id>http://handlino.herokuapp.com/blog/2012/04/07/20594243839</id>
    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<p><img src="http://fireapp.handlino.com/images/logo/logo-500x153.png" alt="Fire.app"/></p>



<p>We have released <a href="http://compass.handlino.com/">Compass.app</a>, the cross-platform designer tool in late 2010. It is already v1.14, and will keep upgrading. Our customers are top level designers around the world. We have also donated 30% of sales to UMDF in favor of Compass.</p>



<p>Today we will introduce our second desktop product: <a href="http://fireapp.handlino.com/">Fire.app</a>.</p>



<p>Fire.app is a designer tool for dead easy HTML prototyping. It has easy-to-use interface just like Compass.app. It not only compile Sass/Compass, but also support Haml, ERB, Markdown, CoffeeScript. It can even build your project into static files, so you can publish to the web server easily.</p>



<p>To thank our lovely customers, if you have bought Compass.app before 2012/4/5, you will receive a free copy of Fire.app.</p>



<p>Please visit <a href="http://fireapp.handlino.com/">Fire.app website</a> to learn more about it. It is only $14 now.</p>
]]></content>
